liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: In another first, three ABC names are vying for the title of Australia's most popular presenter. Australian Story presenter Leigh Sales, Mad as Hell host Shaun Micallef and Mystery Road: Origin actor Mark Coles Smith have all been nominated. They'll face stiff competition from Logies favourite and LEGO Masters host Hamish Blake, who has won the top gong twice — once in 2012 and again last year. Julia Morris, Osher Günsberg and Sonia Kruger are also in the running. "The front person of a program always gets a disproportionate amount of the credit and it's the case on this occasion too," Sales told ABC News. "At both 7.30 and Australian Story, I have worked with the best teams. I reckon it's a mark of how much the public appreciates those two programs."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: You might recognise the comedian from AFL talk show The Front Bar and his appearances on Have You Been Paying Attention? Now Sam Pang is taking on the Logies as the first solo host in 11 years. The 2023 ceremony also marks the first time in more than 30 years that the Logies will be hosted in Sydney. When the location was announced, outgoing New South Wales premier D﻿ominic Perrottet said it would be a game-changer for the state. "This will inject millions of dollars into the NSW economy, creating hundreds of jobs in production, hospitality and events,” he said.
